  "name": "Pot-Controlled RGB Mixer",
  "lesson": {
    "title": "Pot-Controlled RGB Mixer",
    "description": "Three potentiometers each feed an RGB channel through its own 470Ω resistor. Turn one or more pots to dim or brighten red, green, and blue and mix colors on the LED — the same layout as RGB color mixing, but with smooth analog control instead of buttons."
